  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 681996,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection') vulnerability in Apache Airflow Common SQL Provider.\n\nWhen using the partition clause in SQLTableCheckOperator as parameter (which was a recommended pattern), Authenticated UI User could inject arbitrary SQL command when triggering DAG exposing partition_clause to the user.\nThis allowed the DAG Triggering user to escalate privileges to execute those arbitrary commands which they normally would not have.\n\nhttps://lists.apache.org/thread/7tbt8j8d291q3l1rpqs2swdf02rsq5jb",
